{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"129e8223-798f-4589-8da1-9cc682e4bc3e","content":"Good questions — one of those is correct, the other is not.\n\n**`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — ✅ **Correct.** This is the standard .NET MAUI platform-specific API. You need the iOS namespace:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\">\n```\n\nThis adds padding so content avoids the notch/home indicator. Still valid in .NET 10.\n\n**`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid** — ❌ **Not a real property.** There is no `IgnoreSafeArea` property on `Grid` or any layout in .NET MAUI. Your tutorial is likely outdated or confusing frameworks.\n\n### Background image workaround\n\nTo have a background image extend edge-to-edge while keeping content in the safe area, don't use `UseSafeArea` on the page — instead, manage padding manually:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\">\n  <Grid>\n    <!-- Full-bleed background -->\n    <Image Source=\"bg.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n\n    <!-- Content respects safe area via page's SafeAreaInsets -->\n    <StackLayout Padding=\"{OnPlatform iOS='0,47,0,34'}\">\n      <!-- your content -->\n    </StackLayout>\n  </Grid>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nOr programmatically read `On<iOS>().SafeAreaInsets()` to set padding dynamically, which is more robust across devices.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"728c7718-97a1-4dfb-bcc3-571b9bb49377","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't have relevant content. Let me answer based on my knowledge of .NET MAUI safe area APIs.\n\nIn .NET MAUI:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - This is indeed a valid platform-specific property. You need the xmlns: `xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"` and then use `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` on your ContentPage. This is the correct approach.\n\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` - This is NOT a standard .NET MAUI property. \n\nThere's no built-in `IgnoreSafeArea` property on layouts in .NET MAUI. Safe area handling happens at the page level with `UseSafeArea`, so if you want content like a background image to extend beyond the safe area while keeping other content within it, you'd need to use negative margins or other layout workarounds instead. `IgnoreSafeArea` isn't actually a valid .NET MAUI property, so that approach won't work. To get a background image extending past the safe area while keeping content protected, I'd use `UseSafeArea` on the page and then position the background image absolutely or apply negative margins to break it out of the safe area padding.","outputTokens":1085,"requestId":"DC0C:2DE364:1F6ED44:23BBFAA:69F54E4F"},"id":"9c93aa72-51c3-4057-beef-64a1dcea1664","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:07:48.177Z","parentId":"dd9fb1dd-bba6-489b-86a9-e6de4b0bdc65"}
